							<h4>Desktop and Icons</h4>
							
    
							<p> Think about what a desk is; it is a place where you work. People keep things that they use a lot on top of the desk, so they can get them quickly without having to look for them. They save and organize their documents in files and binders and put them in the desk drawers. They safely store all sorts of books, records or anything they want to keep in their desk.</p>	
							<p>The <strong>desktop</strong> on your computer works in much the same way. On the desktop you will see small pictures or symbols, called <strong>icons.</strong> <strong>Icons</strong> are quick ways (or short cuts) to get to the Internet, programs, games or other data stored in the computer. There are other ways to open programs and we will talk about those later. Double clicking with your mouse on an icon opens up a window for whatever it is that the icon represents.</p>
