							<h4>Computer Mouse</h4>
							<br />
							<br />
							<p>A <strong>mouse</strong> is one of the most basic ways for you to do things on your computer. It may be connected to your computer with a wire or it may be wireless.</p>	
							<p>The action of the mouse is seen on the screen as a <strong>pointer.</strong> The pointer is often an arrow (it may also look like a hand) indicating the current location of the mouse on the screen. As you move the mouse (also called mouse pointer), you will see the pointer move on the screen.</p>	
							<p>When you are working with text, the mouse pointer may look different and is called a <strong>cursor,</strong> which looks a little like an upper case letter <strong>"I".</strong></p>	
							<p>This can seem a bit confusing at first, but the <strong>arrow, pointer, mouse pointer and cursor</strong> do pretty much the same things - as you move the computer mouse with your hand, the mouse pointer shows on the screen where you are.</p>
							<img class="img-wrap style1" src="images/computerbasics/cursors.jpg" alt="">
							<br />
							<br />
							<p>To make the best use of your mouse, place it to the side of your computer on a smooth, clean surface such as a mouse pad, rest your hand on top of the mouse and aim it away from you. When you reach the edge of the mouse pad, you can pick up the mouse and change the placement of it in order to keep using it.</p>
							
							<hr>
							<br />
							</div>
							
					<div class="row">
